bib_record.title: Measurements of proton induced g-ray emission cross sections on MgF2 target in the energy range 1.95-3.05 MeV

free_txt: HPGe detector of 20% relative efficiency
placed at an angle of 135 degree relative to the beam
direction at a distance of 6.6 cm from the target.
silicon surface barrier detector placed at
the scattering angle of 165 degree for registration
of the backscattered protons. The mean value of the
particle detector solid angle was 7.5 +- 0.2 msr.
Uncertainty in the proton energy 0.06%
The total uncertainty were determined from the
following partial uncertainties:
Abs. efficiency of the gamma-detector
Stoichiometric ratios from the alpha-RBS
measurement - 2%
Particle detector solid angle - 1%
Rutherford cross section of protons
on the Au - 1%
The proton beam energy was calibrated using the
resonance at 991.88 +- 0.04 keV of the
27Al(p,gamma)28Si reaction and the 7Li(p,n)7Be
reaction threshold at 1880.44 +- 0.02 keV.
Mean proton energies in the target layers were calc.
taking into account the energy loss of protons in the
Au and MgF2 films using SRIM 2003 stopping powers.
Proton beam currents were in the range 10-20 nA.
54.1 ug/cm2 of MgF2 deposited on 6.3 um thin Mylar
foil was used as a target. Additionally 4 nm Au layer
was evaporated on top of the target for normalization.
The number of the F, Mg, and Au atoms per cm2 were
determined by Rutherford backscattering measururements.
